    "History": {
      "rows": [
        [
          "Staff Generated Concept",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "Created By:"
        ],
        [
          "Toreador whose art is making deals, whether Legal or otherwise.",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "Logan Boese"
        ],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "Alexander/Alexandra Carmine - Toreador refugee from Vegas. A former contracts Lawyer, he loves nothing so much as crafting a Deal, the more elaborate, (or better quality,) the Better. Often Opines that they “Should have been a Ventrue.” But they’re not business people, they’re craftsmen. They don’t care about the ends, or what comes after, only the means, and the deals themselves. It doesn’t matter to them if the deal in question is something like a contract dispute, a negotiation between two kindred about territories, whether something is worth a Minor or Major boon, or even just the price of something they’d found on Craigslist. ...Back when they were allowed to USE Craigslist. Since embrace, has often been used as a negotiator, and was one of the first to catch wind of what was happening in Vegas. Only escaped because they cashed in a Major Boon from a previous deal. Had some Mob contacts, but “They’re probably dead.” ALWAYS looking to Cut a deal, they Love it. Not obsessed or psychotic about it, but they’ll take the opportunity if it presents itself. It is, after all, their Art. Feels very naked here, with few, (If any,) previous contacts in LA, and wants to build up at least a small stockpile of at least minor boons. Doesn’t think there’s anything left in Vegas, so is perfectly willing to resettle here if they think they can get a “practice” thriving again, (Essentially, would like to build up their reputation as an expert negotiator). Has also begun to realize how hard it is to admire the small deals, and so has turned their eye to making longer-lasting, larger deals. They want to make one that “Lasts.” and “Matters.”"
        ],
        [
          "Sire:",
          "Bernie Conrad",
          "Reference: (If any)",
          "",
          "",
          "Clan",
          "Toreador - Entranced by Art"
        ],
        [
